\[4abc + ab + bc + ca - 2a - 2b - 2c + 1 = 449.\]This factors as $(2a + 1)(2b + 1)(2c + 1) = 449.$  Since $a \ge b \ge c,$ $2a + 1 \ge 5,$ so $2b + 1$ and $2c + 1$ are both less than or equal to 5.  Hence, we can guess $2b + 1 = 3$ and $2c + 1 = 1.$  This gives us $a = 112,$ so the smallest possible value of $N$ is $abc = \boxed{112}.$

